256
00:14:57,484 --> 00:14:58,892
Well, what are the alternatives?

257
00:15:01,474 --> 00:15:03,417
Well, if I didn't fell so guilty I'd,

258
00:15:04,237 --> 00:15:05,731
I'd do what I should have done in the first place:

259
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:08,595
just move dad and Daphne into their own appartment.

260
00:15:08,596 --> 00:15:10,142
Oh, for goodness sake, Frasier.

261
00:15:10,143 --> 00:15:11,933
It hasn't been that long, you have to give it a chance.

262
00:15:12,526 --> 00:15:14,882
And you might remember why you moved him in in the first place.

263
00:15:15,383 --> 00:15:16,407
Refresh me.

264
00:15:17,024 --> 00:15:18,680
You wanted to get closer to dad.

265
00:15:18,681 --> 00:15:19,906
I still do.

266
00:15:20,430 --> 00:15:21,835
There isn't anything I'd like more,

267
00:15:21,836 --> 00:15:22,960
but he makes it impossible.

268
00:15:22,961 --> 00:15:24,675
I can't read my book, I can't have my coffee,

269
00:15:24,676 --> 00:15:26,520
I can't have any peace in my own home.

270
00:15:26,916 --> 00:15:28,833
So what you're saying is, you want to be closer to dad,

271
00:15:28,834 --> 00:15:30,468
but you don't actually want him around.

272
00:15:35,741 --> 00:15:39,533
Ask yourself Frasier, have you tried to sit down and talk to him

